ecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Gibbons was born about 1475, in Rolvenden, Kent, England, his father, Jervis Gibbons, was 26 and his mother, Mrs Jervis Gibbons, was 22. He married Margaret about 1500, in Rolvenden, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 3 daughters. He died on 18 November 1546, in Rolvenden, Kent, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 72."},"et":{"about 1475–18 November 1546":"umbes 1475–18. november 1546","1475–1546":"1475–1546","1483–Male":"1483–Surnud","1490–1548":"1490–1548","1483–1547":"1483–1547","1498–1551":"1498–1551","1500–1547":"1500–1547","1502–Female":"1502–Surnud","1504–1578":"1504–1578","1506–1571":"1506–1571","1450–Male":"1450–Surnud","1455–Female":"1455–Surnud","1450":"1450","1571":"1571","1483":"1483","1490":"1490","1547":"1547","1502":"1502","1546":"1546","1578":"1578","1500":"1500","18 November 1546":"18. november 1546","1455":"1455","1498":"1498","1475":"1475","1551":"1551","about 1500":"umbes 1500","about 1475":"umbes 1475","1506":"1506","1504":"1504","1548":"1548","Benenden, Kent, England":"Benenden, Kent, England","Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, England","Rolvenden, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Rolvenden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1475–18 November 1546":"noin 1475–18. marraskuuta 1546","1475–1546":"1475–1546","1483–Male":"1483–Kuollut","1490–1548":"1490–1548","1483–1547":"1483–1